      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-700">
              <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-white font-semibold">Plan</th>
              <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-white font-semibold">API Calls/Month</th>
              <th class="py-3 text-white font-semibold">Price</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-dark-300">
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-800">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Community</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">1,000</td>
              <td class="py-3">Free</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-800">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Individual</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">10,000</td>
              <td class="py-3">$9.99/month</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-800">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Team</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">100,000</td>
              <td class="py-3">$25/user/month</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-800">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Enterprise</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Unlimited</td>
              <td class="py-3">$55/user/month</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="text-dark-300 mb-4">
        <strong class="text-white">What counts as an API call:</strong> Each skill search, skill detail
        request, recommendation request, or installation counts as one API call.
      </p>

      <p class="text-dark-300 mb-4">
        <strong class="text-white">Exceeding limits:</strong> When you reach your monthly limit, API
        requests will be rate-limited until the next billing cycle. You will receive notifications
        at 80%, 90%, and 100% of your quota.
      </p>

      <p class="text-dark-300">
